#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/meta/fbnic.rst:10
msgid ""
"fbnic has three components stored on the flash which are provided in one "
"PLDM image:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/meta/fbnic.rst:13
msgid ""
"fw - The control firmware used to view and modify firmware settings, request "
"firmware actions, and retrieve firmware counters outside of the data path. "
"This is the firmware which fbnic_fw.c interacts with."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/meta/fbnic.rst:16
msgid ""
"bootloader - The firmware which validate firmware security and control basic "
"operations including loading and updating the firmware. This is also known "
"as the cmrt firmware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/meta/fbnic.rst:19
msgid "undi - This is the UEFI driver which is based on the Linux driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/meta/fbnic.rst:21
msgid ""
"fbnic stores two copies of these three components on flash. This allows "
"fbnic to fall back to an older version of firmware automatically in case "
"firmware fails to boot. Version information for both is provided as running "
"and stored. The undi is only provided in stored as it is not actively "
"running once the Linux driver takes over."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/meta/fbnic.rst:27
msgid ""
"devlink dev info provides version information for all three components. In "
"addition to the version the hg commit hash of the build is included as a "
"separate entry."
msgstr ""

